-- Emerson Electric says order growth slowing
-- 
-- Tue Nov 28, 2006 8:59am EST
-- http://www.reuters.com/article/2006/11/28/us-emersonelectric-orders-idUSWEN037320061128

 

 BOSTON  (Reuters) - Diversified manufacturer Emerson Electric Co. ( EMR.N ) said on Tuesday in a filing with the U.S. Securities and Exchange Commission that its order growth rate slowed to 5 percent for the three months ended in October. 

 The company said that is down from a growth rate of 5 to 10 percent for the three months ended in September and 10 to 15 percent for the three months ended in August. Emerson said orders at its climate technologies unit were down 10 to 15 percent for the three months ended in October, were flat to up 5 percent at its appliance and tools unit for the period, were up 5 to 10 percent at its network power unit and were up 10 to 15 percent at its process management and industrial automation units.